						<summary>

						<p>Same wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">••••• [Pā]ṇḍyadēva: Year 11 = 1276 A.D. (Vīrapāṇḍya)</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is damaged in some places. It records a gift of a <hi rend="italic">sandhyā</hi> lamp and a sum of 10 <hi rend="italic">paṇam</hi> for (providing oil for) it, to the same deity by a certain Śiṅgakaramiṇḍaṉ Dēvaṉ (second name lost), a Veḷḷāḻaṉ Kaḻañjaya of Nambipērūr in Vaḍapariśāra-nāḍu. The gift was received by the same <hi rend="italic">Śivabrāhmaṇas</hi> who figure in No. 218 above, etc.</p>						

						</summary>
